    think='The blank screen issue is reproducible when running individually too.
This means `clearState: true` is causing the app to show a blank screen sometime
s when it starts.\n\nThis is a known Flutter/Maestro issue. When `clearState: tr
ue` is used, Maestro clears the app\'s data and then launches it. But Flutter ap
ps sometimes take a moment to render the first frame after a cold start with cle
ared data.\n\nThe fix is to add a wait after `launchApp: clearState: true`. But 
the core-beliefs.md says not to use `sleep`. We should use `extendedWaitUntil` o
r `assertVisible` with a longer timeout.\n\nBut `assertVisible` is what\'s faili
ng! The issue is that the default timeout for `assertVisible` might not be long 
